#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.3"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.3:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.3:0.2"
msgid "1. Bhaṇḍagāmavagga"
msgstr "1. At Bhaṇḍa Village"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.3:0.3"
msgid "3. Paṭhamakhatasutta"
msgstr "3. Broken (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.3"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: abyatto → avyatto (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an4.3:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bālo abyatto asappuriso khataṃ "
"upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo ca viññūnaṃ, bahuñca "
"apuññaṃ pasavati."
msgstr ""
"“When a foolish, incompetent bad person has four qualities they keep "
"themselves broken and damaged. They deserve to be blamed and criticized by "
"sensible people, and they make much bad karma."

msgctxt "an4.3:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi catūhi?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "an4.3:1.3"
msgid "Ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā avaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, "
msgstr ""
"Without examining or scrutinizing, they praise those deserving of criticism, "

msgctxt "an4.3:1.4"
msgid "ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā vaṇṇārahassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, "
msgstr "and they criticize those deserving of praise. "

msgctxt "an4.3:1.5"
msgid "ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā appasādanīye ṭhāne pasādaṃ upadaṃseti, "
msgstr "They arouse faith in things that are dubious, "

msgctxt "an4.3:1.6"
msgid "ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā pasādanīye ṭhāne appasādaṃ upadaṃseti—"
msgstr "and they don’t arouse faith in things that are inspiring."

msgctxt "an4.3:1.7"
msgid ""
"imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato bālo abyatto asappuriso "
"khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo ca viññūnaṃ, "
"bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavati."
msgstr ""
"When a foolish, incompetent bad person has these four qualities they keep "
"themselves broken and damaged. They deserve to be blamed and criticized by "
"sensible people, and they make much bad karma."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: viyatto → vyatto (bj, pts1) | byatto (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an4.3:2.1"
msgid ""
"Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato paṇḍito viyatto sappuriso akkhataṃ "
"anupahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, anavajjo ca hoti ananuvajjo ca viññūnaṃ, "
"bahuñca puññaṃ pasavati."
msgstr ""
"When an astute, competent good person has four qualities they keep "
"themselves healthy and whole. They don’t deserve to be blamed and criticized "
"by sensible people, and they make much merit."

msgctxt "an4.3:2.2"
msgid "Katamehi catūhi?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "an4.3:2.3"
msgid "Anuvicca pariyogāhetvā avaṇṇārahassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, "
msgstr ""
"After examining and scrutinizing, they criticize those deserving of "
"criticism, "

msgctxt "an4.3:2.4"
msgid "anuvicca pariyogāhetvā vaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, "
msgstr "and they praise those deserving of praise. "

msgctxt "an4.3:2.5"
msgid "anuvicca pariyogāhetvā appasādanīye ṭhāne appasādaṃ upadaṃseti, "
msgstr "They don’t arouse faith in things that are dubious, "

msgctxt "an4.3:2.6"
msgid "anuvicca pariyogāhetvā pasādanīye ṭhāne pasādaṃ upadaṃseti—"
msgstr "and they do arouse faith in things that are inspiring."

msgctxt "an4.3:2.7"
msgid ""
"imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato paṇḍito viyatto sappuriso "
"akkhataṃ anupahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, anavajjo ca hoti ananuvajjo ca "
"viññūnaṃ, bahuñca puññaṃ pasavatīti."
msgstr ""
"When an astute, competent good person has these four qualities they keep "
"themselves healthy and whole. They don’t deserve to be blamed and criticized "
"by sensible people, and they make much merit."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.3:3.1"
msgid "Yo nindiyaṃ pasaṃsati,"
msgstr "When you praise someone worthy of criticism,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.3:3.2"
msgid "Taṃ vā nindati yo pasaṃsiyo;"
msgstr "or criticize someone worthy of praise,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.3:3.3"
msgid "Vicināti mukhena so kaliṃ,"
msgstr "you choose bad luck with your own mouth:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.3:3.4"
msgid "Kalinā tena sukhaṃ na vindati."
msgstr "you’ll never find happiness that way."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.3:4.1"
msgid "Appamatto ayaṃ kali,"
msgstr "Bad luck at dice is a trivial thing,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.3:4.2"
msgid "Yo akkhesu dhanaparājayo;"
msgstr "if all you lose is your money"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.3:4.3"
msgid "Sabbassāpi sahāpi attanā,"
msgstr "and all you own, even yourself."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.3:4.4"
msgid "Ayameva mahantataro kali;"
msgstr "What’s really terrible luck"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.3:4.5"
msgid "Yo sugatesu manaṃ padosaye."
msgstr "is to hate the holy ones."

# Here’s the math, following Vanarata’s method as mention by BB: koti=10,000,000 pakoti=10¹⁴ kotipakoti=10²¹ nahuta=10²⁸ ninnahuta=10³⁵ abbuda=10⁴² nirabbuda=2×10⁴³ Sataṃ chattiṃsatī sahassānaṃ nirabbudānaṃ=136,000×2×10⁴³=2.72×10⁴⁸ pañca sahassānaṃ ca abbudāni=5000×10⁴²=5×10⁴⁵
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.4"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an4.3:5.1"
msgid "Sataṃ sahassānaṃ nirabbudānaṃ,"
msgstr "For more than two quinquadecillion years,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.3:5.2"
msgid "Chattiṃsatī pañca ca abbudāni;"
msgstr "and another five quattuordecillion years,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Yamariyagarahī → yamarīyaṃ garahiya (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an4.3:5.3"
msgid "Yamariyagarahī nirayaṃ upeti,"
msgstr "a slanderer of noble ones goes to hell,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.3:5.4"
msgid "Vācaṃ manañca paṇidhāya pāpakan”ti."
msgstr "having aimed bad words and thoughts at them.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.3:5.5"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
